    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "Contract Employee kept in quarters overnight due to prior neck injury concerns",
      "Contract Employee transported to Abbeville General for medical treatment the following morning",
      "BSEE Lafayette District conducted onsite investigation on 6 March 2014"
    ],
    "summary": "On 1 March 2014 at approximately 2215 hours, a Contract Employee injured his neck as he rolled his ankle while stepping on a piece of grating on the production deck near the High Pressure Separator. The employee possibly stepped on a small gap measuring slightly less than 2 inches or tripped on a small piece of plate covering a hole. As he fell forward, his head came in contact with a junction box, injuring his neck. The employee was treated at Abbeville General and released to his personal physician with a possible neck sprain diagnosis.",
